snippet.textDisplay:
I'm worried that this will be treated like the Zika and Ebola outbreaks. You hear about them once they're in home countries and then coverage stops after a while.

With everything that's going on in the world, climate change and virus evolution to name the biggest problems, things have to change, mentality has to change. I'm sorry for those who live and are visiting Wuhan, but they need to stay where they are. It'll help officials monitor their conditions and prevent it from spreading quicker than by natural means. I get people want to go home and "get away" from the virus, but I'm going to be blunt: It doesn't matter if you were there before the outbreak, the citizens of Wuhan were there before the outbreak too. YOU ARE INFECTED and your body is housing the disease. Viruses want one thing, to spread and multiply. Just like people, they want to live, reproduce, and expand. The best thing to do is to stay within the quarantine zones and wait it out. Support efforts will come up with ways to help those not from Wuhan, but taking them out is not a good idea
